      • WeblogicApp

        public WeblogicApp(java.util.Date timestamp,
                   java.lang.String servername,
                   java.lang.String appname,
                   java.lang.String app_state,
                   int opensessions_currentcount)
        Constructs a WeblogicApp using given parameters. This object provides a unique, immutable, Weblogic application set of metrics.
        Parameters:
        timestamp -
        servername - Name of the server where the application is registered
        appname - Name of the application
        app_state - State of the application. See Weblogic documentation on ApplicationStateRuntimeMBean.getCurrentState() for possible values.
        opensessions_currentcount - Number of currently open sessions for the application.
